        </nav>
        <div class="tut-content">

          <div class="tut-sec" id="bg-what">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">What is GeM Bidding?</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar navy"></div>
            <p class="tut-p">The Government e-Marketplace (GeM) is India's official procurement portal for government departments, ministries, PSUs, defence, railways, schools and hospitals. When a government buyer needs products above ₹3 lakh, or wants competitive pricing through multiple sellers, they create a <strong>Bid</strong> — inviting all registered sellers to quote their prices.</p>
            <p class="tut-p">This creates healthy competition, ensures the buyer gets the best value, and provides a fully transparent, audit-proof record of the procurement process.</p>
            <div class="tut-callout warn"><strong>Did you know?</strong>Many GeM bids receive zero or very few responses — not because the product doesn't exist, but because sellers either aren't aware of the bid or aren't authorised for that product category. This leads to procurement failures and delayed deliveries for government departments.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="tut-sec" id="bg-categories">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Product Categories — Q1 to Q4</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar navy"></div>
            <p class="tut-p">GeM classifies all products into four quadrants based on seller eligibility. Understanding these categories is critical — the category determines who can respond to your bid and what competition to expect.</p>
            <div class="tut-cards">
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🔒</div><div class="tut-card-title">Q1 — OEM Exclusive</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Only the Original Equipment Manufacturer can sell. No resellers, no distributors. Examples: specific defence equipment, exclusive branded electronics.<br><br><strong style="color:#DC2626">We cannot participate in Q1 bids.</strong></div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🏢</div><div class="tut-card-title">Q2 — Authorised Sellers</div><div class="tut-card-desc">OEM and officially authorised resellers only. GeM requires proof of brand authorisation. Examples: HP, Dell, Lenovo laptops; Canon/Epson printers.<br><br><strong style="color:#1D4ED8">We participate for brands we are authorised to represent.</strong></div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">✅</div><div class="tut-card-title">Q3 — Open + Branded</div><div class="tut-card-desc">OEM, authorised resellers and unbranded alternatives can all participate. Broadest category — best competition. Examples: office furniture, stationery, basic electronics.<br><br><strong style="color:#15803D">Fully supported — all brands and options.</strong></div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🌐</div><div class="tut-card-title">Q4 — Open Market</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Any GeM registered seller can participate without authorisation. Maximum competition. Examples: general consumables, basic tools, commodities.<br><br><strong style="color:#6D28D9">Fully supported — no restrictions.</strong></div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="tut-callout tip"><strong>Quick guide</strong>When creating your bid, check the product's Q category first. Q3 and Q4 bids attract the most responses and competitive pricing. Q2 bids require you to confirm the product is available through an authorised seller before publishing.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="tut-sec" id="bg-types">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Types of GeM Bids</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar navy"></div>
            <p class="tut-p">GeM offers three main bidding formats. Each suits a different type of procurement requirement.</p>
            <div class="tut-cards">
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📉</div><div class="tut-card-title">Reverse Auction (RA)</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Sellers bid downward during a time-limited window (4–24 hours). The seller with the lowest final bid wins. Best for standard, catalogue products where multiple sellers compete. Consistently delivers 15–30% below catalogue price.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📋</div><div class="tut-card-title">BOQ Bid</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Bill of Quantities — used when you need multiple different items in one procurement. Sellers quote for the entire list or selected line items. Best for office fit-outs, school/hospital equipment, or any multi-item requirement.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🔧</div><div class="tut-card-title">Custom Bid</div><div class="tut-card-desc">For products or services not in GeM's standard catalogue. You describe the requirement in detail — specs, quantity, delivery terms. Sellers respond with proposals and pricing. Best for specialised equipment or non-standard items.</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="tut-callout info"><strong>Which to use?</strong>Standard products → Reverse Auction. Multiple items → BOQ Bid. Specialised or unlisted items → Custom Bid. Above ₹3 lakh, one of these three is mandatory — Direct Purchase is not permitted.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="tut-sec" id="bg-why">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Why GeM Bids Often Go Unfulfilled</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar navy"></div>
            <p class="tut-p">Despite GeM's reach, many government bids close without a single valid response. Understanding the common reasons helps you structure bids that attract quality responses.</p>
            <div class="tut-cards">
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🔐</div><div class="tut-card-title">Missing Brand Authorisation</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Q2 bids require brand authorisation that many sellers don't have. Always confirm authorisation availability before setting Q2 as a requirement.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📦</div><div class="tut-card-title">Mismatched Specifications</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Bid specifications that don't align with GeM catalogue listings mean sellers can't respond even if they have the product. Keep specs broad enough to allow catalogue matching.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📍</div><div class="tut-card-title">Delivery Constraints</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Remote locations or unrealistic delivery deadlines deter most sellers. Our 15+ partner network enables delivery to most pincodes across India.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">⭐</div><div class="tut-card-title">Quality Concerns</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Fear of receiving substitutes discourages buyers from using GeM. We provide written product confirmation — exact brand, model and specs — before any order is placed.</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tut-sec" id="bg-how">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">How Hues MyIndia Helps</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar navy"></div>
            <p class="tut-p">We are a GeM registered supplier with a network of 15+ authorised partner firms across India. We specialise in ensuring your government procurement bids receive quality responses — genuine brands, authorised products, on-time delivery, and full GeM documentation compliance.</p>
            <div class="tut-steps">
              <div class="tut-step"><div class="tut-step-left"><div class="tut-step-num navy">1</div><div class="tut-step-line navy"></div></div><div class="tut-step-content"><div class="tut-step-title">You Share the Bid Requirement</div><div class="tut-step-desc">Submit your bid number, product details, quantity and delivery location. We respond within 4 working hours.</div></div></div>
              <div class="tut-step"><div class="tut-step-left"><div class="tut-step-num navy">2</div><div class="tut-step-line navy"></div></div><div class="tut-step-content"><div class="tut-step-title">We Confirm Availability and Category</div><div class="tut-step-desc">We verify the product is available in the right Q category, check our partner network, and confirm delivery feasibility to your location.</div></div></div>
              <div class="tut-step"><div class="tut-step-left"><div class="tut-step-num navy">3</div><div class="tut-step-line navy"></div></div><div class="tut-step-content"><div class="tut-step-title">Written Product Confirmation</div><div class="tut-step-desc">Before any bid response is submitted, we provide a written confirmation of exact product brand, model and specifications.</div></div></div>
              <div class="tut-step"><div class="tut-step-left"><div class="tut-step-num navy">4</div></div><div class="tut-step-content"><div class="tut-step-title">We Respond to the Bid on GeM</div><div class="tut-step-desc">Our registered partner firm responds to the bid with competitive pricing. Once the order is placed, we fulfil with full documentation — GST invoice, e-way bill, delivery challan.</div></div></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tut-sec" id="bg-faq">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar navy"></div>
            <div class="faq-list">
              <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the minimum bid duration on GeM?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">The minimum bid duration on GeM is typically 3 days for standard bids and 4 hours for Reverse Auctions. Buyers can set longer durations to attract more responses. Shorter durations tend to receive fewer bids as sellers need time to verify product availability and pricing.</div></div>
              <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I create a bid for a product not listed on GeM?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">Yes — use a Custom Bid. You describe your requirement in detail (specifications, quantity, delivery location, technical parameters) and sellers respond with proposals. Custom bids are ideal for specialised equipment or items that do not have a standard catalogue listing on GeM.</div></div>
              <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What happens if no seller responds to my bid?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">If no seller responds, you have three options: re-publish the bid with revised specifications or relaxed delivery conditions; extend the bid duration to allow more sellers to respond; or, if the item is not available on GeM after reasonable attempts, proceed with offline quotation procurement under GFR 2017 Rule 144 with documentation of your GeM search attempts.</div></div>
              <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I split a bid award between multiple sellers?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">Yes — for BOQ bids, you can split the award at the line item level. Different line items can be awarded to different sellers if no single seller can fulfil the entire BOQ. This is done at the bid evaluation stage, not during bid creation.</div></div>
              <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is there a value limit for GeM bids?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">There is no upper limit for GeM bids — you can bid for any value. For purchases between ₹25,001 and ₹3 lakh, direct purchase is allowed but bids are also permitted. Above ₹3 lakh, a bid or reverse auction is mandatory. There is no minimum bid value.</div></div>
              <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can we bid for products under MGNREGS or other central schemes through GeM?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">Yes — GeM can be used for procurement funded by MGNREGS material components, 15th Finance Commission grants, PM-POSHAN, Jal Jeevan Mission and other central schemes, subject to the scheme's approved activity list and financial norms. Always verify that the product category is eligible under the specific scheme before creating a bid.</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tut-cta navy">
            <div class="tut-cta-tag">Get Your Bid Fulfilled</div>
            <div class="tut-cta-h">Ready to participate in a GeM bid?</div>
