        <div class="tut-content">

          <div class="tut-sec" id="oq-what">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">What is Quotation Based Procurement?</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar amber"></div>
            <p class="tut-p">Quotation based procurement is a method where the buying department invites written price quotations from suppliers before placing a purchase order. It is governed by the General Financial Rules (GFR) 2017, specifically Rule 144, which mandates that for purchases above ₹25,000 and up to ₹2,50,000, a minimum of three quotations must be obtained from different suppliers.</p>
            <p class="tut-p">This process ensures transparency, competitive pricing and audit compliance — without requiring departments to go through a full tender process or use the GeM portal.</p>
            <div class="tut-callout tip"><strong>Key point</strong>Quotation based procurement is a legitimate, audit-accepted method of purchase. It does not require GeM registration and is fully valid under GFR 2017 for eligible purchase values.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="tut-sec" id="oq-who">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Who Can Use This?</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar amber"></div>
            <p class="tut-p">Any government-funded institution that is not mandatorily required to use GeM — or that falls below the GeM-mandatory threshold — can use quotation based procurement.</p>
            <div class="tut-cards">
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🏫</div><div class="tut-card-title">Schools &amp; Colleges</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Government schools, KVs, state board colleges, polytechnics and universities receiving government grants.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🏥</div><div class="tut-card-title">Hospitals &amp; Health Centres</div><div class="tut-card-desc">District hospitals, PHCs, sub-centres, AYUSH centres and NHM facilities.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🏘️</div><div class="tut-card-title">Gram Panchayats</div><div class="tut-card-desc">All gram panchayats, block offices and panchayat samitis across India.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🏛️</div><div class="tut-card-title">Autonomous Bodies</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Registered societies, boards, councils and government-funded trusts.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🏢</div><div class="tut-card-title">Local Bodies</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Municipal corporations, town committees and urban local bodies.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">⚖️</div><div class="tut-card-title">Departments Not on GeM</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Central and state departments not yet onboarded to GeM, or for items not available on the portal.</div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="tut-callout info"><strong>Even if your department is on GeM</strong>For items not available on the portal, or for urgent requirements below the mandatory threshold, quotation based procurement is a valid and accepted alternative.</div>
          </div>

          <div class="tut-sec" id="oq-gfr">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">GFR 2017 Rule 144 — Purchase Value Limits</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar amber"></div>
            <p class="tut-p">Rule 144 of GFR 2017 sets clear purchase value thresholds that determine the procurement method required.</p>
            <div class="tut-cards">
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">💰</div><div class="tut-card-title">Up to ₹25,000</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Direct purchase from any supplier. Single quotation sufficient. Approved by head of office.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📋</div><div class="tut-card-title">₹25,001 – ₹2,50,000</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Minimum 3 quotations from different suppliers required. Comparative statement mandatory. Select most suitable quote.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📢</div><div class="tut-card-title">Above ₹2,50,000</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Open tender or GeM mandatory. Quotation route not applicable above this value threshold.</div></div>
            </div>
            <p class="tut-p">After receiving quotations, the department prepares a comparative statement listing all quotes received. The lowest or most suitable quotation is selected, a purchase order is raised, and supply is completed with full documentation.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="tut-sec" id="oq-docs">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Documents You Will Receive</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar amber"></div>
            <p class="tut-p">Every supply through Hues MyIndia comes with complete government-standard documentation — ensuring your purchase file is complete for audit and accounts purposes.</p>
            <div class="tut-cards">
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📄</div><div class="tut-card-title">Quotation on Letterhead</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Formal price quotation on GST-registered firm letterhead, with HSN code, GST rate and unit pricing.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📊</div><div class="tut-card-title">Comparative Statement</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Ready-to-file comparative statement of quotations for your purchase file — audit ready.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🧾</div><div class="tut-card-title">GST Tax Invoice</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Full tax invoice with GSTIN, HSN code, applicable GST rate and item-wise breakup.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📦</div><div class="tut-card-title">Delivery Challan</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Proof of dispatch and delivery for your records and payment processing.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🚛</div><div class="tut-card-title">E-Way Bill</div><div class="tut-card-desc">For consignments above the threshold — generated for inter-state or large value orders.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🏷️</div><div class="tut-card-title">Warranty Certificate</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Manufacturer warranty card or certificate where applicable to the product.</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tut-sec" id="oq-how">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">How It Works</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar amber"></div>
            <div class="tut-steps">
              <div class="tut-step"><div class="tut-step-left"><div class="tut-step-num amber">1</div><div class="tut-step-line amber"></div></div><div class="tut-step-content"><div class="tut-step-title">Share Your Requirement</div><div class="tut-step-desc">Tell us what you need — product name, specifications, quantity and estimated budget. Attach a tender notice or spec sheet if available.</div></div></div>
              <div class="tut-step"><div class="tut-step-left"><div class="tut-step-num amber">2</div><div class="tut-step-line amber"></div></div><div class="tut-step-content"><div class="tut-step-title">Receive Official Quotations</div><div class="tut-step-desc">We issue formal quotations within 4 working hours — properly formatted on letterhead with GST details, HSN codes and pricing.</div></div></div>
              <div class="tut-step"><div class="tut-step-left"><div class="tut-step-num amber">3</div><div class="tut-step-line amber"></div></div><div class="tut-step-content"><div class="tut-step-title">Prepare Comparative Statement</div><div class="tut-step-desc">Using the quotations received, prepare your comparative statement. Select the most suitable quotation as per your department's norms.</div></div></div>
              <div class="tut-step"><div class="tut-step-left"><div class="tut-step-num amber">4</div><div class="tut-step-line amber"></div></div><div class="tut-step-content"><div class="tut-step-title">Raise Purchase Order</div><div class="tut-step-desc">Issue a purchase order to the selected supplier. We acknowledge and confirm delivery timeline.</div></div></div>
              <div class="tut-step"><div class="tut-step-left"><div class="tut-step-num amber">✓</div></div><div class="tut-step-content"><div class="tut-step-title">Supply with Full Documentation</div><div class="tut-step-desc">Products delivered with GST invoice, delivery challan, e-way bill and warranty documents. Your purchase file is complete.</div></div></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tut-sec" id="oq-faq">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar amber"></div>
            <div class="faq-list" id="oq-faq-list">
              <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can a department on GeM use quotation procurement?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">Yes — for items not available on GeM, or for genuine urgent requirements, departments registered on GeM can use quotation-based procurement under GFR 2017 Rule 144. Document your GeM search result showing unavailability before proceeding.</div></div>
              <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the maximum purchase value under Rule 144?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">₹2,50,000 (two lakh fifty thousand). For purchases above this value, open tender or GeM is mandatory. Quotation procurement is valid only between ₹25,001 and ₹2,50,000 (where 3 quotes are required) and up to ₹25,000 (single quote).</div></div>
              <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do all 3 quotations have to be from different companies?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">Yes — quotations must be from genuinely independent suppliers. Getting quotes from related companies, group firms, or obviously coordinated submissions is a serious audit violation. The three suppliers must have different GST numbers and ideally different owners.</div></div>
              <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do I have to select the lowest quotation?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">Not necessarily. You must select the "most suitable" quotation — which is usually the lowest, but can be a higher-priced quote if there are documented quality, delivery or specification reasons. The comparative statement must clearly explain any deviation from the lowest quote.</div></div>
              <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How quickly can Hues MyIndia provide quotations?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">We issue formal quotations within 4 working hours of receiving your complete requirement. For urgent requirements, contact us via WhatsApp — we can expedite for same-day quotation in most cases.</div></div>
              <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I get all 3 required quotations from Hues MyIndia?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">No — all 3 quotations must be from genuinely different suppliers. We can provide 1 of the 3 required quotations. You will need to obtain the other 2 from other independent suppliers. We can advise on how to identify other suppliers for your requirement if needed.</div></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="tut-cta amber">
            <div class="tut-cta-tag">Ready to Procure?</div>
            <div class="tut-cta-h">Get your quotations within 4 hours.</div>
            <p class="tut-cta-p">Share your product requirement and we'll send GFR-compliant quotations for your purchase file — fully audit ready.</p>
