          <a onclick="document.getElementById('tut-q-3').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">Q2 — Authorised Only</a>
          <a onclick="document.getElementById('tut-q-4').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">Q3 — Open + Branded</a>
          <a onclick="document.getElementById('tut-q-5').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">Q4 — Open Market</a>
          <a onclick="document.getElementById('tut-q-6').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">Which Can We Supply?</a>
        </nav>
        <div class="tut-content">
          <div class="tut-sec" id="tut-q-1">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">What are Q Categories?</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar indigo"></div>
            <p class="tut-p">GeM assigns every product listing a "Quadrant" (Q1 to Q4) that defines who is eligible to sell it. This classification is based on seller authorisation — specifically whether the seller needs to be the original manufacturer, an authorised dealer, or can be any registered seller.</p>
            <div class="tut-callout info"><strong>Why it matters</strong>The category of a product directly determines how many sellers can bid on your requirement. Q4 products attract the most competition; Q1 products can only be supplied by the manufacturer itself.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tut-sec" id="tut-q-2">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Q1 — OEM Exclusive</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar indigo"></div>
            <p class="tut-p">Only the Original Equipment Manufacturer (OEM) can list and sell Q1 products on GeM. These are typically highly specialised items where the government wants to ensure authenticity and direct manufacturer accountability.</p>
            <div class="tut-callout warn"><strong>Note</strong>We cannot supply Q1 category products as we are not an OEM for any product. If your bid is Q1, it will be handled exclusively by the manufacturer.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tut-sec" id="tut-q-3">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Q2 — Authorised Resellers Only</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar indigo"></div>
            <p class="tut-p">Q2 products can be sold by the OEM or by sellers who hold an official authorisation certificate from the OEM. This ensures brand authenticity while allowing a wider seller network.</p>
            <p class="tut-p">We can supply Q2 products for brands where we or our partner firms hold GeM authorisation. Limited brands available — contact us to confirm before bidding.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tut-sec" id="tut-q-4">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Q3 — Open Market + Branded</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar indigo"></div>
            <p class="tut-p">Q3 allows OEMs, authorised resellers, and also unbranded/generic alternatives to participate. This is the broadest category for branded products — multiple sellers can offer the same specification at competitive prices.</p>
            <div class="tut-callout tip"><strong>Best for buyers</strong>Q3 bids typically receive the highest number of responses, giving your department the best pricing and choice.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="tut-sec" id="tut-q-5">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Q4 — Full Open Market</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar indigo"></div>
            <p class="tut-p">Q4 requires no brand authorisation. Any registered GeM seller can participate. These are typically commodity items — stationery, cleaning supplies, basic electrical components — where brand is secondary to specification and price.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tut-sec" id="tut-q-6">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Which Categories Can We Supply?</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar indigo"></div>
            <div class="tut-cards">
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🔒</div><div class="tut-card-title">Q1 — Not Available</div><div class="tut-card-desc">OEM exclusive. We cannot supply Q1 products.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🏢</div><div class="tut-card-title">Q2 — Limited Brands</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Available for authorised brands only. Confirm availability before bidding.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">✅</div><div class="tut-card-title">Q3 — Full Availability</div><div class="tut-card-desc">We can supply all Q3 category products. Best competition and pricing.</div></div>
              <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🌐</div><div class="tut-card-title">Q4 — Full Availability</div><div class="tut-card-desc">All Q4 products available. No authorisation needed.</div></div>
            </div>

          <div class="tut-sec" id="q-faq">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar indigo"></div>
            <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How do I know which Q category a product is in?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">The category is shown on the GeM product listing page. When you search for a product, each listing shows its seller eligibility category. You can also filter by category when creating a bid.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can a Q4 product be listed as Q2 by a seller?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">No — the Q category is assigned by GeM based on the product type, not the seller's choice. Sellers must meet the eligibility criteria for the category they list under. Misrepresentation of category is a violation of GeM's seller terms.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the difference between Q3 and Q4?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">Q3 allows branded and unbranded products but requires the seller to meet some qualification criteria. Q4 is fully open — any registered GeM seller can participate, regardless of brand authorisation or any other qualification. Q4 is typically for commodity items.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can we get Q1 products through Hues MyIndia?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">No — Q1 products can only be supplied by the OEM (Original Equipment Manufacturer) directly. We cannot supply Q1 category products as we are not an OEM for any product. If your requirement is Q1, contact the manufacturer directly.</div>
        </div>
        </div>
          </div>
            <div class="tut-cta indigo">
              <div class="tut-cta-tag">Submit Your Bid</div>
              <div class="tut-cta-h">Ready to participate in a GeM bid?</div>
