        <h1 class="tut-h1">How to Place a Direct Purchase<br>on GeM — Step by Step</h1>
        <p class="tut-hero-p">Direct purchase is the simplest way to buy on GeM — no bid, no auction. Here is the complete step-by-step process, including limits, rules and what to do when L1 is not available.</p>
        <div class="tut-meta"><span class="tut-pill">📦 6 min read</span><span class="tut-pill">All Buyers</span><span class="tut-pill">GeM Portal</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wrap"><div class="tut-body">
      <nav class="tut-toc">
        <div class="tut-toc-title">Contents</div>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('dp-1').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">What is Direct Purchase?</a>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('dp-2').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">Value Limits</a>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('dp-3').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">Step-by-Step Process</a>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('dp-4').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">L1 Price — Explained</a>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('dp-5').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">Common Problems</a>
      </nav>
      <div class="tut-content">
        <div class="tut-sec" id="dp-1">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">What is Direct Purchase on GeM?</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar navy"></div>
          <p class="tut-p">Direct Purchase (also called L1 Purchase) is the process of buying a product directly from the GeM portal without creating a bid or reverse auction. You search for the product, select the seller offering the lowest price (L1), add to cart and raise a purchase order — all in a few minutes.</p>
          <div class="tut-callout tip"><strong>When to use it</strong>Use direct purchase for standard, off-the-shelf products at lower quantities. For specialised items or large quantities, bids give you better pricing through competition.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tut-sec" id="dp-2">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Value Limits for Direct Purchase</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar navy"></div>
          <div class="tut-cards">
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">💰</div><div class="tut-card-title">Up to ₹25,000</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Direct purchase from any listed seller. No requirement to select L1 — you may choose any seller based on quality, delivery time or brand preference.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📋</div><div class="tut-card-title">₹25,001 – ₹3 Lakh</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Must select L1 (lowest priced) seller. If fewer than 3 sellers are available, you must justify the selection. Comparative statement maintained automatically by GeM.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🏷️</div><div class="tut-card-title">Above ₹3 Lakh</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Mandatory to use Bid or Reverse Auction. Direct purchase is not permitted above this threshold — ensures competitive pricing for larger procurement.</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tut-sec" id="dp-3">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Step-by-Step Direct Purchase Process</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar navy"></div>
          <div class="tut-steps">
            <div class="tut-step"><div class="tut-step-left"><div class="tut-step-num navy">1</div><div class="tut-step-line navy"></div></div><div class="tut-step-content"><div class="tut-step-title">Log in to GeM</div><div class="tut-step-desc">Go to gem.gov.in and log in with your buyer credentials. Ensure your organisation and consignee location are correctly set in your profile.</div></div></div>
            <div class="tut-step"><div class="tut-step-left"><div class="tut-step-num navy">2</div><div class="tut-step-line navy"></div></div><div class="tut-step-content"><div class="tut-step-title">Search for the Product</div><div class="tut-step-desc">Use the search bar or browse categories. Apply filters — brand, specifications, delivery state, MSME preference, Make in India — to narrow results to your requirement.</div></div></div>
            <div class="tut-step"><div class="tut-step-left"><div class="tut-step-num navy">3</div><div class="tut-step-line navy"></div></div><div class="tut-step-content"><div class="tut-step-title">Verify Specifications</div><div class="tut-step-desc">Before adding to cart, check the product specifications carefully. Ask for seller confirmation if the listing name differs from your required brand or model.</div></div></div>
            <div class="tut-step"><div class="tut-step-left"><div class="tut-step-num navy">4</div><div class="tut-step-line navy"></div></div><div class="tut-step-content"><div class="tut-step-title">Add to Cart and Raise PO</div><div class="tut-step-desc">Add the required quantity, select the consignee (delivery address), and raise the Purchase Order. The PO is sent to the seller immediately.</div></div></div>
            <div class="tut-step"><div class="tut-step-left"><div class="tut-step-num navy">5</div></div><div class="tut-step-content"><div class="tut-step-title">Confirm Receipt and Process Payment</div><div class="tut-step-desc">Once goods arrive, confirm receipt on the GeM portal. This triggers the PFMS payment workflow. Payment reaches the seller within the timelines specified in the PO.</div></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tut-sec" id="dp-4">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">What is L1 Price on GeM?</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar navy"></div>
          <p class="tut-p">L1 (Lowest 1) is the lowest price listed for a product among all sellers on GeM at the time of your search. For purchases above ₹25,000, you must select the L1 seller. The GeM portal automatically identifies and displays the L1 price — you cannot justify selecting a higher-priced seller without documented reasons (e.g., L1 seller cannot deliver to your location, or product specifications don't match).</p>
          <div class="tut-callout warn"><strong>Important</strong>L1 price changes in real time as sellers update their listings. The price at the time of raising the PO is the final price — not the price when you searched earlier. Always confirm before raising the PO.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tut-sec" id="dp-5">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Common Problems and How to Solve Them</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar navy"></div>
          <div class="tut-callout warn"><strong>Product not found on GeM</strong>Search with alternative keywords, HSN code or category name. If still not found, document the search and proceed with offline procurement under GFR 2017 Rule 144.</div>
          <div class="tut-callout warn"><strong>L1 seller cannot deliver to your location</strong>This is a valid reason to go to L2. Document clearly that L1 was contacted and could not fulfil delivery. Maintain this on file.</div>
          <div class="tut-callout warn"><strong>Listing name is different from required product</strong>Request a written confirmation from the seller that the product being supplied matches your required brand and model. We provide this confirmation for every order.</div>

          <div class="tut-sec" id="dp-faq">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar navy"></div>
            <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the direct purchase limit on GeM in 2025?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">For central government departments, the direct purchase limit is ₹3 lakh. Above ₹3 lakh, a Bid or Reverse Auction is mandatory. State departments may have different limits — check your state's GeM directive.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I place a direct purchase without selecting L1?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">For purchases below ₹25,000, you can select any seller. For ₹25,001–₹3 lakh, you must select the L1 (lowest priced) seller. Deviating from L1 requires documented justification.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How long does a seller have to accept a GeM purchase order?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">The seller has 48 hours to accept a Purchase Order on GeM. If not accepted within this period, the PO is automatically cancelled and you must re-place the order or approach the next seller.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I cancel a GeM purchase order after placing it?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">Yes — buyers can cancel a Purchase Order before the seller accepts it, or after acceptance with valid reasons. Cancellation after dispatch may attract a cancellation charge as per the seller's terms.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What if the product is out of stock after I raise the PO?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">If the seller cannot fulfil due to stock shortage, they must reject the PO with a reason. You can then place an order with the next L1 seller. Document the rejection for your purchase file.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I negotiate the L1 price with the seller?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">No direct negotiation is allowed on GeM. Prices are set by sellers and compete through market forces. For large requirements, use Reverse Auction — prices drop through competition without manual negotiation.</div>
        </div>
        </div>
          </div>
          <div class="tut-cta navy"><div class="tut-cta-tag">Skip the Hassle</div><div class="tut-cta-h">We'll find the GeM link for you.</div><p class="tut-cta-p">Tell us what you need — we check GeM availability and share the direct purchase link within 2 hours.</p><button class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" onclick="openReq()">🔍 Request a Product</button></div>
        </div>
