    </div></div>
  </div><!-- /pg-tut-direct-purchase -->

  <!-- ═══ ARTICLE: What Documents Are Required ═══ -->
  <div id="pg-tut-documents" style="display:none">
    <div class="tut-hero amber">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="tut-back" onclick="goPage('knowledge')">← Back to Knowledge Hub</div>
        <div class="tut-tag">Compliance</div>
        <h1 class="tut-h1">What Documents Are Required<br>for GeM Procurement?</h1>
        <p class="tut-hero-p">A complete checklist of every document your department needs — from purchase indent to final delivery receipt — for a clean, audit-proof GeM purchase file.</p>
        <div class="tut-meta"><span class="tut-pill">📋 7 min read</span><span class="tut-pill">All Departments</span><span class="tut-pill">Audit Compliance</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wrap"><div class="tut-body">
      <nav class="tut-toc">
        <div class="tut-toc-title">Contents</div>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('doc-1').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">Why Documentation Matters</a>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('doc-2').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">Pre-Purchase Documents</a>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('doc-3').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">During Order Documents</a>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('doc-4').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">Delivery Documents</a>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('doc-5').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">Offline Procurement Docs</a>
      </nav>
      <div class="tut-content">
        <div class="tut-sec" id="doc-1">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Why Documentation Matters</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar amber"></div>
          <p class="tut-p">Every government purchase is subject to audit — internal audit, CAG (Comptroller and Auditor General) audit, and vigilance inspections. A purchase file with missing or incorrect documents is the most common reason for audit observations, stoppage of payment and personal liability for the procuring officer.</p>
          <p class="tut-p">Maintaining a complete purchase file is not just a procedural requirement — it protects you personally from audit risk and demonstrates compliance with GFR 2017 and GeM guidelines.</p>
          <div class="tut-callout warn"><strong>Audit reality</strong>CAG reports consistently flag incomplete purchase files as a major procurement irregularity. The most common missing documents are the purchase indent, comparative statement and written product confirmation before ordering.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tut-sec" id="doc-2">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Pre-Purchase Documents</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar amber"></div>
          <div class="tut-cards">
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📝</div><div class="tut-card-title">Purchase Indent</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Signed internal document from the requiring department specifying exact product, quantity, specifications, estimated budget and urgency. Must be approved by the Head of Office before procurement begins.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🔍</div><div class="tut-card-title">GeM Search Documentation</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Screenshot or printout of your GeM search result — especially if the product is not available on GeM and you are proceeding offline. Required for audit trail.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">✅</div><div class="tut-card-title">Written Product Confirmation</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Written statement from the seller confirming that the GeM listing matches your required brand, model and specifications — before any order is placed. Critical for preventing substitution.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🏛️</div><div class="tut-card-title">Financial Sanction</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Approval from the competent financial authority (as per your department's delegation of powers) before placing the order. The sanctioning authority's designation must match the purchase value.</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tut-sec" id="doc-3">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">During Order Documents</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar amber"></div>
          <div class="tut-cards">
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📋</div><div class="tut-card-title">GeM Purchase Order</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Automatically generated by the GeM portal when you confirm the order. Contains all details — seller, product, quantity, price, delivery terms. Download and retain in the purchase file.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📊</div><div class="tut-card-title">Comparative Statement (offline)</div><div class="tut-card-desc">For offline procurement only — a table listing all quotations received, with price comparison and selection justification. Not required for GeM purchases as GeM generates this automatically.</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tut-sec" id="doc-4">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Delivery and Post-Delivery Documents</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar amber"></div>
          <div class="tut-cards">
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🧾</div><div class="tut-card-title">GST Tax Invoice</div><div class="tut-card-desc">From the seller — must show GSTIN, HSN code, product description, quantity, unit price, GST rate and total. This is the basis for your payment processing and accounts records.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📦</div><div class="tut-card-title">Delivery Challan</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Document accompanying the goods during transit — shows what was dispatched, in what quantity. Required for matching with your receipt note.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🚛</div><div class="tut-card-title">E-Way Bill</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Required for goods consignments above ₹50,000 moving interstate or intrstate (state-specific rules apply). The seller generates this — retain a copy for your file.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">✍️</div><div class="tut-card-title">Receipt & Inspection Note</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Signed document from your storekeeper / receiving officer confirming goods were received, inspected and found to be as per specification. Triggers payment on GeM.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🏷️</div><div class="tut-card-title">Warranty Certificate</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Manufacturer warranty card or certificate where applicable. Must be in the name of your organisation for warranty claims to be valid.</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tut-sec" id="doc-5">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Additional Documents for Offline Procurement (GFR 2017)</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar amber"></div>
          <p class="tut-p">For offline quotation-based procurement under GFR 2017 Rule 144, you additionally need minimum 3 quotations from different suppliers on their letterhead, your comparative statement, and the selected supplier's GSTIN and PAN details for records.</p>
          <div class="tut-callout tip"><strong>We provide all offline documents</strong>Our quotations are formatted specifically for GFR 2017 compliance — with GSTIN, PAN, HSN codes, GST breakup and unit pricing — ready to file without modification.</div>

          <div class="tut-sec" id="doc-faq">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar amber"></div>
            <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is a comparative statement required for GeM purchases?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">No — for GeM Direct Purchases and Bids, the GeM portal itself serves as the comparative statement. The price comparison among sellers is transparent on the portal and does not require a separate document. A comparative statement is required only for offline quotation-based procurement.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the purpose of the purchase indent?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">The purchase indent is an internal document that initiates the procurement process. It specifies what is needed, why, in what quantity and at what estimated cost. It must be signed by the head of the requiring section and approved by the competent authority before any purchase action begins.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do I need a written confirmation of product match for every GeM order?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">Yes — especially when the GeM listing name differs from your required product brand or model. A written confirmation from the seller that the product being supplied matches your requirement protects you from substitution disputes and is increasingly required by audit authorities.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How long should procurement documents be retained?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">Procurement files must be retained for a minimum of 3 years after the financial year of purchase for routine items. For assets (equipment, furniture), retain until the asset is disposed of. High-value or contentious procurements may require longer retention.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Is a receipt note different from a delivery challan?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">Yes. The delivery challan is issued by the seller and accompanies the goods during transit. The receipt note (or goods receipt note/GRN) is issued by your organisation's storekeeper after inspecting and accepting the goods. Both are required in your purchase file.</div>
        </div>
        </div>
          </div>
