  <!-- ═══ ARTICLE: Schools and Hospitals on GeM ═══ -->
  <div id="pg-tut-schools-hospitals" style="display:none">
    <div class="tut-hero indigo">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="tut-back" onclick="goPage('knowledge')">← Back to Knowledge Hub</div>
        <div class="tut-tag">GeM for Institutions</div>
        <h1 class="tut-h1">How Government Schools &amp; Hospitals<br>Can Use GeM Portal</h1>
        <p class="tut-hero-p">Government schools, hospitals, PHCs and aided institutions can procure through GeM. This guide explains eligibility, registration, what you can buy, and how to handle items not on GeM.</p>
        <div class="tut-meta"><span class="tut-pill">🏫 7 min read</span><span class="tut-pill">Schools &amp; Hospitals</span><span class="tut-pill">Aided Institutions</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="wrap"><div class="tut-body">
      <nav class="tut-toc">
        <div class="tut-toc-title">Contents</div>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('sh-1').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">Are Schools Eligible?</a>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('sh-2').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">What Schools Buy on GeM</a>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('sh-3').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">Are Hospitals Eligible?</a>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('sh-4').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">What Hospitals Buy on GeM</a>
        <a onclick="document.getElementById('sh-5').scrollIntoView({behavior:'smooth',block:'start'})">When to Use Offline Route</a>
      </nav>
      <div class="tut-content">
        <div class="tut-sec" id="sh-1">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Are Government Schools Eligible for GeM?</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar indigo"></div>
          <p class="tut-p">Yes — all government schools are eligible to register on GeM and procure through the portal. This includes Kendriya Vidyalayas, Navodaya Vidyalayas, state government schools, government-aided schools receiving grants, and higher secondary institutions under state education departments.</p>
          <p class="tut-p">Registration is done through the school's authorised administrative officer (typically the Principal or District Education Officer). A government email ID is required. Aided schools using government grants for procurement are also covered under GeM's mandate.</p>
          <div class="tut-callout info"><strong>KVS and NVS</strong>Kendriya Vidyalaya Sangathan and Navodaya Vidyalaya Samiti schools are mandated to use GeM for all eligible procurements. Each school has a designated procurement officer for GeM operations.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tut-sec" id="sh-2">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">What Can Schools Buy on GeM?</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar indigo"></div>
          <div class="tut-cards">
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🖥️</div><div class="tut-card-title">IT Equipment</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Computers, laptops, projectors, printers, scanners, UPS and networking equipment for smart classrooms and labs.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🪑</div><div class="tut-card-title">Furniture</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Student desks, chairs, teacher tables, almirahs, whiteboards and library furniture — all available in multiple grades.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">📚</div><div class="tut-card-title">Stationery & Supplies</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Notebooks, pens, chalk, marker boards, art supplies, printing paper and office consumables.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🧪</div><div class="tut-card-title">Lab Equipment</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Science lab apparatus, chemicals, glassware and safety equipment for physics, chemistry and biology labs.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">💡</div><div class="tut-card-title">Electrical</div><div class="tut-card-desc">LED lights, fans, switches, wiring materials and solar panels — BIS-certified products for school buildings.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🏃</div><div class="tut-card-title">Sports Equipment</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Cricket, football, volleyball equipment and athletic gear under Khelo India and state sports programmes.</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tut-sec" id="sh-3">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Are Government Hospitals Eligible for GeM?</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar indigo"></div>
          <p class="tut-p">Yes — all government hospitals, district hospitals, primary health centres (PHCs), community health centres (CHCs), and NHM (National Health Mission) facilities are eligible and encouraged to use GeM. Many state health departments have issued specific circulars mandating GeM for drug procurement, medical equipment and hospital consumables.</p>
          <div class="tut-callout tip"><strong>CMSS and TNMSC</strong>Some states procure drugs and medical supplies through centralised state procurement agencies (like CMSS in UP or TNMSC in Tamil Nadu). For such items, follow your state agency's process. For non-formulary and equipment items, GeM is typically the route.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tut-sec" id="sh-4">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">What Can Hospitals Buy on GeM?</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar indigo"></div>
          <div class="tut-cards">
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🏥</div><div class="tut-card-title">Medical Equipment</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Pulse oximeters, BP monitors, stethoscopes, weighing scales, ECG machines, ultrasound equipment and surgical instruments.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🛏️</div><div class="tut-card-title">Hospital Furniture</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Hospital beds, stretchers, wheelchairs, IV stands, examination tables and waiting area chairs.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🧤</div><div class="tut-card-title">PPE & Consumables</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Gloves, masks, gowns, syringes, IV lines and other single-use consumables not covered by central drug procurement.</div></div>
            <div class="tut-card"><div class="tut-card-icon">🧹</div><div class="tut-card-title">Housekeeping & Security</div><div class="tut-card-desc">Cleaning services, housekeeping consumables, disinfectants and security services available under GeM services category.</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tut-sec" id="sh-5">
          <h2 class="tut-sec-h">When Should Schools and Hospitals Use Offline Procurement?</h2>
          <div class="tut-sec-bar indigo"></div>
          <p class="tut-p">Use offline procurement under GFR 2017 Rule 144 when the required item is not available on GeM, when your institution is not yet registered on GeM, or when the procurement is for a specialised item that GeM's standard catalogue does not cover adequately (such as custom lab equipment or specialised medical devices).</p>
          <div class="tut-callout warn"><strong>Document first</strong>Before proceeding offline, always conduct and document a GeM search. Your purchase file must show that you checked GeM and the item was either unavailable or did not meet your specifications.</div>

          <div class="tut-sec" id="sh-faq">
            <h2 class="tut-sec-h">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="tut-sec-bar indigo"></div>
            <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can a government-aided school (private management, government grant) use GeM?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">Yes — if your school receives government grants and the procurement is from those grant funds, you are eligible to register on GeM as a buyer. Contact your District Education Officer or the state education department's GeM nodal officer for registration assistance.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can a KV (Kendriya Vidyalaya) place GeM orders independently?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">KVS has a centralised procurement structure. Individual KVs place orders on GeM for smaller items, while larger procurement (like IT equipment) is handled centrally by KVS headquarters or regional offices. Check your KV's delegation of powers and procurement manual.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Are drugs and medicines available on GeM for hospitals?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">Some drugs and medical supplies are listed on GeM. However, many state governments procure essential medicines through centralised state agencies (like CMSS, TNMSC). Check your state health department's procurement policy to understand which route applies to which items.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can a private hospital empanelled under Ayushman Bharat buy on GeM?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">No — GeM is only for government organisations and public sector entities. Private hospitals, even if empanelled under government schemes, cannot register as buyers on GeM.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the process for a PHC to get GeM registration?<div class="faq-icon">+</div></div>
          <div class="faq-a">PHC registration is typically handled at the District Health Officer (DHO) or Chief Medical Officer (CMO) level. The DHO registers as a buyer and delegates purchasing authority to PHCs under their jurisdiction. Contact your district NHM or health department office.</div>
        </div>
        </div>
          </div>
          <div class="tut-cta indigo"><div class="tut-cta-tag">We Help Both Routes</div><div class="tut-cta-h">GeM or offline — we handle both.</div><p class="tut-cta-p">We supply to government schools and hospitals across India — GeM purchase link or formal quotation, delivered within 2 hours.</p><button class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" onclick="goPage('services')">View Our Services →</button></div>
